{
  "texts": [
    "Given Lemma 6.20, we need only explain what to do with each safe Sahlqvist implication ψ → χ.",
    "First, using propositional logic, rewrite ψ as an equivalent disjunction ψ 1 ∨ • • • ∨ ψ n where each ψ k is a conjunction of boxed atoms and negative formulas.",
    "Then rewrite ψ → χ as the equivalent conjunction 1≤k≤n (ψ k → χ), which is a safe Sahlqvist formula.",
    "Then by Lemma 6.20.2, it suffices to find a local correspondent for each implication ψ k → χ.",
    "Using the equivalence of (α ∧ β) → γ and α → (¬β ∨ γ), pull out any negative conjuncts from ψ k, negate them, and disjoin them with the consequent."
  ]
}